# Vault (knowledge paths)

Consult `vault_storage.md` in this framework for the full lifecycle table and templates.

## Moves (after user approval)

- Input from `queue/`: after a summary exists, move the source file to `queue/processed/`. After that move, reset `queue/notes.md` to empty (standing scratch file for the next notes).
- Summary in `summaries/`: after content is integrated into topics, move it to `summaries/processed/`.
- Archive: only move a topic from `topics/` to `archive/topics/` when the user agrees it is obsolete.

## Topic file sections (active topics in `topics/`)

Use the structure in `vault_storage.md` (Current State, Decisions, Open Questions, Key People, Pending Outbound, Outbound Log, References).

## Reference knowledge (`knowledge/*.md` except `glossary.md`)

Stable reference articles -- no required template or durable-topic lifecycle sections. Freeform.

## Glossary (`knowledge/glossary.md`)

Reserved term index; always read on orient/parse when working under the knowledge root. See `vault_storage.md` section on glossary. Not a durable topic.

## Summaries

Match the summary template in `vault_storage.md` (Source, Date, Topics links, Key Points, Decisions, Action Items).
